### Is this a regression?

- [X] Yes, this behavior used to work in the previous version

### The previous version in which this bug was not present was

16

### Description

`globalThis.ng` is replaced by minified function ng

I don't know exactly how angular uses `globalThis`, but I think `globalThis.ng` is quite important, and **should not** be replaced by minified content

### Minimal Reproduction

https://github.com/cheng93/ng-globalThis

Install and build `elements`, then serve it with `node server.js`
Install and build `my-app`, then serve it with `node server.js`

my-app will pull in elements, which will overrwrite `globalThis.ng` with the minified `ng` function. This function is could be anything and it depends on how much functions you have.

For my case it's

```js
function ng(t, e, n) {
  let [r, o] = [+c(t.start), +c(t.end)].sort((a, u) => a - u),
    [i, s] = [+c(e.start), +c(e.end)].sort((a, u) => a - u);
  return n?.inclusive ? r <= s && i <= o : r < s && i < o;
}
```

### Exception or Error

```js
ngOnInit(): void {
    console.log((globalThis as any).ng);
    console.log((globalThis as any).ng.ɵcompilerFacade);
    scripts.forEach(loadScript);
    setTimeout(() => {
      console.log((globalThis as any).ng);
      console.log((globalThis as any).ng.ɵcompilerFacade);
    }, 1000);
  }
```


